The course provides a hands-on introduction to Estonian criminal trial advocacy. Students will learn to make opening statements and closing arguments; examine witnesses; handle physical evidence and illustrative materials; make objections and argue motions. The course ends in a simulated trial.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to offer students skills training in making tactical choices as criminal trial attorneys.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Knows: - general tenets of adversarial criminal procedure - the order of criminal trial and law applicable Skills: - opening statements - Examination of witnesses and presentation of documents and physical evidence - Closing arguments - Developing case theory and planning the presentation of evidence
